    <section id="sec-6" class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">6. Security Analysis</h2>
      <h3 id="sec-6.1" class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">6.1 &ldquo;Classical&rdquo; Attacks</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300">Statistical attacks (differential and linear cryptanalysis) exploit S-box patterns propagated through linear layers. The Flystel has low differential uniformity and MDS diffusion ensures many active S-boxes. Integral attacks and invariant subspaces are prevented by the non-aligned round structure.</p>
      <h3 id="sec-6.2" class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">6.2 Algebraic Attacks</h3>
      <div class="formal-block formal-block-definition">
        <div class="formal-block-title text-blue-400">Definition 3 (CICO)</div>
        <div class="formal-block-content"><p class="text-gray-300">Let <span class="math">P : \mathbb&#123;F&#125;_q^2 \to \mathbb&#123;F&#125;_q^2</span> be a permutation. Find <span class="math">(\text&#123;in&#125;, \text&#123;out&#125;)</span> such that <span class="math">P(0, \text&#123;in&#125;) = (0, \text&#123;out&#125;)</span>.</p></div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-300"><strong>6.2.1 Intermediate variables.</strong> Modeling 1 introduces <span class="math">2n_r</span> equations. The standard zero-dimensional strategy: compute a DRL Gr&ouml;bner basis, then FGLM to LEX.</p>
      <div class="formal-block formal-block-claim">
        <div class="formal-block-title text-cyan-400">Estimate 1 (Even characteristic)</div>
        <div class="formal-block-content"><p class="text-gray-300">Cost estimated by FGLM: <span class="math">\mathcal&#123;O&#125;(\ell n_r \cdot 9^&#123;\omega \ell n_r&#125;)</span>.</p></div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-300"><strong>6.2.2 Odd characteristic.</strong></p>
      <div class="formal-block formal-block-claim">
        <div class="formal-block-title text-cyan-400">Conjecture 1</div>
        <div class="formal-block-content"><p class="text-gray-300"><span class="math">d_&#123;\text&#123;exp&#125;&#125; \geq 2n_r + \kappa_\alpha</span>, where <span class="math">\kappa_3 = 1</span>, <span class="math">\kappa_5 = 2</span>, <span class="math">\kappa_7 = 4</span>, <span class="math">\kappa_9 = 7</span>, <span class="math">\kappa_&#123;\alpha \geq 11&#125; = 9</span>.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="formal-block formal-block-claim">
        <div class="formal-block-title text-cyan-400">Estimate 2 (Odd characteristic)</div>
        <div class="formal-block-content"><p class="text-gray-300">Cost estimated by Gr&ouml;bner basis: <span class="math">\mathcal&#123;O&#125;\!\left(\binom&#123;d_&#123;\text&#123;exp&#125;&#125; + 2n_r&#125;&#123;2n_r&#125;^\omega\right)</span>.</p></div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-300">Two extra rounds are added as a conservative measure.</p>
    </section>

