    <section id="app-a" class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Appendix A. Details of our Security Analysis</h2>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">A.1 Differential and Linear Attacks</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300">Differential uniformity is 4 (<span class="math">\text&#123;Flystel&#125;_2</span>) or <span class="math">\alpha - 1</span> (<span class="math">\text&#123;Flystel&#125;_p</span>). Best differential probability per S-box: <span class="math">(\alpha-1)/q^2</span>. With <span class="math">q &gt; 2^&#123;63&#125;</span>, 3 active S-boxes suffice for 128-bit security. Linearity is conjectured at most <span class="math">p \log p</span>.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">A.2 Integral Attacks</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300">The open Flystel is a 3-round Feistel with a permutation in the center round, so word-level patterns cannot propagate past two full rounds. Subgroup-based attacks are prevented by the internal additions and constants.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">A.3 Invariant Subspaces</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300">The invariant set has probability <span class="math">1/q</span> per column. The non-linear pattern is broken by the constant addition and linear layer.</p>
    </section>

